# apps/mobile/.env.example  (issue #55 — native billing)
#
# Copy to apps/mobile/.env.local and fill in. .env.local is gitignored and is
# NEVER read, printed, or committed. Everything here is EXPO_PUBLIC_* on purpose:
# these values ship in the app bundle and are safe to expose. There are NO secrets
# in the mobile app. When a key is absent the app falls back to the in-memory mock
# billing provider, so it still runs in Expo Go, in CI, and with no store setup.

# RevenueCat PUBLIC SDK keys (one per platform). RevenueCat dashboard:
#   Project settings > API keys > "Public app-specific" keys.
#   iOS  key starts with "appl_",  Android key starts with "goog_".
# These only allow reads and purchases, never account changes, so they are public.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_IOS_KEY="appl_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_KEY="goog_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"

# Web backend base URL used ONLY to cross check the account entitlement against the
# server (GET /api/entitlements/current). Optional: RevenueCat is the on-device
# source of truth, so gating works without it.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL="https://YOUR_DOMAIN"

# Local testing helper for the MOCK provider only (ignored once a RevenueCat key is
# set). Force the simulated purchase outcome so every paywall state is verifiable
# before real store products exist: success | cancelled | pending | error.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_BILLING_MOCK_OUTCOME="success"

# Local testing helper for deep/universal links (issue #65). Simulate a COLD START
# from a tapped link WITHOUT a real device: the app behaves as if launched by this
# URL and routes to the mapped screen after the auth + reader gates. A real launch
# URL always takes precedence. Leave unset in real builds. Examples:
#   bedtimequests://story/starlight-sail  |  https://bedtimequests.com/collection
# EXPO_PUBLIC_LINK_INITIAL_URL="bedtimequests://story/starlight-sail"
